  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks @vvo for pointing me to this issue. The query hook would definitely work for my use case and it is really flexible. It would allow developers to cancel the search in certain circumstances (like #4), debounce, delay the search, do different things on different input values etc.\n\nI'd suggest one addition which would be very helpful to another scenario I have. It would be great if the `search` function passed to the `queryHook` function accepts an `inputValue` argument. This way you would be able to pass a modified input to the search based on certain conditions.\n",
